verbs.description: untrim (third-person singular simple present untrims, present participle untrimming, simple past and past participle untrimmed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To remove the trimmings or adornments from.
examples: She was trimming a very smart straw hat with pink ribbons; trimming and untrimming, for the bows were tied and untied, taken off and put on, and taken off again, with a look of impatience and discontent  […]

entries.meaning: (computer graphics, CAD) To restore the original shape of (a surface that has been trimmed).
